The paper deals with the design of a jamming-resilient communication system using physical layer secret keys. This involves techniques related to cryptography (cs.CR), information theory (cs.IT), wireless networking (cs.NI), control systems (cs.SY), and software-defined radio (cs.MM). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CR, followed by cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, and cs.MM.
